 :tx/rationale "Create task: C9-STEER-1v3: CLI_COHERENCE_SPEC §4 output templates + INV-CLI-006 progressive disclosure + INV-CLI-002 vocabulary for observe subcommands. PROBLEM: (1) AgentOutput is a receipt, not steering. (2) Default output is 1142 lines (violates INV-CLI-006 ≤10). (3) No --verbose flag for progressive disclosure. (4) Vocabulary inconsistent ('obs', 'results' vs canonical 'observations'). APPROACH: (A) Add --verbose bool flag to ObserveAction::List, Search, Show, Recent in mod.rs. (B) DEFAULT mode (≤10 lines): Line 1: count + group count. Lines 2-8: top 7 concepts by member_count (name + count + developmental stage: <20=sensorimotor, 20-50=concrete, >50=formal). Line 9: '... N more concepts (--verbose for full list)' if truncated. Line 10: SteeringVector question. (C) VERBOSE mode: full listing per concept with individual observations. (D) AGENT mode: context=scope, content=top 3 concepts + structural gap (≤200 tokens via safe_truncate_bytes), footer=question + command. Agent gets a DISTILLED steering vector, not a receipt and not a dump. (E) SEARCH output: 'search QUERY: N observations' (not 'results'). Top 5 ranked rows. SteeringVector. (F) SHOW output: DetailOutput template. (G) RECENT output: ListOutput variant. (H) ALL outputs use canonical vocabulary 'observation(s)' per INV-CLI-002 §6. (I) JSON output includes concept_membership + structural_gap + steering_question keys for forward-compatibility with STEER-2v2. ACCEPTANCE: (A) Default observe list ≤10 lines. (B) --verbose shows full listing. (C) Agent mode contains concept names (not just counts). (D) No occurrence of 'obs' abbreviation or 'results' in observe output — only 'observation(s)'. (E) All 4 subcommands match their §4 template. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs (add --verbose to ObserveAction), crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs (all run_* functions)"
